<MELItem itemNbr="28-22-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-28-22-01.1.2-28-22-01">
<Title>Main Tank Fuel Pumps</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="4" nbrRequired="3" maintIndicator="(M)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be inoperative provided: </Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Inoperative pump is deactivated.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Main tank quantity indications operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Deactivate the inoperative fuel pump (AMM DDG 28-22-01).</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>For left main tank aft pump inoperative, using a flight deck multi-function display only, open circuit breaker BOOST PUMP-AFT L and lock with an INOP tag.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For left main tank forward pump inoperative, using a flight deck multi-function display only, open circuit breaker BOOST PUMP-FWD L and lock with an INOP tag.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For right main tank aft pump inoperative, using a flight deck multi-function display only, open circuit breaker BOOST PUMP-AFT R and lock with an INOP tag.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>For right main tank forward pump inoperative, using a flight deck multi-function display only, open circuit breaker BOOST PUMP-FWD R and lock with an INOP tag.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
<OperationNote>
<Para>Associated fuel pump switch is selected off.</Para>
</OperationNote>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
